BFN 

  [Text] Shiraz, Fars Prov. May 23, IRNA -- The second and 
third phases of the military exercise code-named `Ra'ad 7' 
(Thunder) were successfully launched Sunday night and Monday 
morning in Darengon region of Shiraz, capital of the southern 
province of Fars. 
  Several army units, including the infantry, artillery and 
airborne, took part in the military exercise, carried out in an 
area of 150 square kilometers. The first phase of the maneuver 
was launched in the same region Sunday morning. 
  A number of local military officials, including military 
commander of Fars Brigadier General Ahmad Dadbin, who described 
the military exercise as successful, inspected the maneuver. 

